sorry for the delay but thanks for your feedback. I added constraints for Xi and Yi and switch to feets instead of meters (Sharelock don't use metric system obviously)

I don't think knowledge is an issue : convex hull is a common algorithm, and it's not hard to solve it without knowledge of these algorithm. Implementation is simple as well. I found many other CG puzzle more complicated or requiring more knowledge (graph, pathfinding). Maybe geometry problems are not common here...

@player_one : thanks for the "rewrite" and you're experience is a good synthesis of why i designed this puzzle :-) , but he magic trick is a secret ... ;-)
